  29 Mar 2004; Lars Weiler <pylon@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  stable on ppc, as it is a dependency for net-mail/exim-4.24-r3

  18 Mar 2004; Grant Goodyear <g2boojum@hotmail.com> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Adding additional ppc64, hppa, and ia64 keywords that broke ssmtp.

  18 Mar 2004; Jon Portnoy <avenj@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild :
  AMD64 keywords.

  18 Mar 2004; Grant Goodyear <g2boojum@hotmail.com> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Added ~alpha.  My sincere apologies for all of the archs I broke yesterday!

  18 Mar 2004; David Holm <dholm@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Added to ~ppc.

  18 Mar 2004; Joshua Kinard <kumba@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Added ~mips to KEYWORDS.

  17 Mar 2004; Jason Wever <weeve@gentoo.org> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Added ~sparc keyword so you can now emerge ssmtp and postfix without it dying
  due to bad dependencies.

  17 Mar 2004; Grant Goodyear <g2boojum@hotmail.com> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  Updated the ebuild to remove the protection that had kept users
  from overwriting /usr/sbin/sendmail.  Now that we're gearing up to
  have all mtas install mailwrapper this protection is unwanted.

*mailwrapper-0.1 (08 Mar 2004)

  08 Mar 2004; Grant Goodyear <g2boojum@hotmail.com> mailwrapper-0.1.ebuild:
  New ebuild.

